Mini project: Command Line calculator

Create a command line Calculator using argparse
3 argumanets
    1. num1 (type=float)
    2. operator (choices=["add","sub","mul"])
    3. num2 (type=float)

    ("num1",type=float,help="")

put condition:
    args.operator == "add"
        result = args.num1 + args.num2


Run the above Script: py calc.py 56 mul 2

